<P><H1 align=center>ASSIGN APPLICANTS AND GUARANTORS – CR050</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P>If there is more than one customer on the application, it needs to be 
registered whether they are both applicants or whether one is an applicant and 
one is a guarantor. On this screen the applicant added second can be made the 
first named on the application.</P>
<P>If there is only one applicant, this option is not available.</P>
<P><H3>Applicants : </H3>the names of the customers will appear 
in this box. To make the second applicant the first named on the application, 
highlight the second applicant and click on ‘Move Up’.
<P></P>
<P>To assign one of the applicants as a guarantor, highlight the name and click 
on ‘Guarantor’. The name will then appear in the ‘Guarantors’ box at the bottom 
of the screen.</P>
<P><H3>Guarantors: </H3>any applicant(s) assigned as guarantors 
will appear in this box. To reassign as applicants, highlight the name and click 
on ‘Applicants’. The name will then appear in the ‘Applicants’ box at the top of 
the screen.
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>clicking on OK leads back to <A href="HELP_CR030.asp">Customer Application Summary 
(CR030)</A>
<P></P>

